el)#1987: Vanity Fair: BBC miniseries starring Eve Matheson as Becky Sharp, Rebecca Saire as Amelia Sedley, James Saxon as Jos Sedley and Simon Dormandy as Dobbin.|Vanity Fair]]'' (1987) (TV)<br />''[[Vanity Fair (1998 TV serial)|Vanity Fair]]'' (1998) (TV)<br />''[[Vanity Fair (2004 film)|Vanity Fair]]'' (2004)\n|-\n| ''Vanity Row'' (1953), [[W. R. Burnett]]\n| ''[[Accused of Murder]]'' (1956)\n|-\n| ''Vennelalo Adapilla'' (1991), [[Yandamuri Veerendranath]]\n| ''[[Beladingala Baale]]'' (1995)\n|-\n| ''[[Vengeance (Jonas book)|Vengeance]]'' (1984),<ref>Although ''Vengeance'' is concerned with real people and events, it is a fictional representation of history.</ref> [[George Jonas]]\n| ''[[Sword of Gideon]]'' (1986), George Jonas and [[Chris Bryant]]<br />''[[Munich (film)|Munich]]'' (2005)\n|-\n| ''Vengeance Valley'' (1949), [[Luke Short (writer)|Luke Short]]\n| ''[[Vengeance Valley]]'' (1951)\n|-\n| ''A Very Private Gentleman'' (1990), [[Martin Booth]]\n| ''[[The American (2010 film)|The American]]'' (2010)\n|-\n| ''[[Vespers in Vienna]]'' (1947), [[Bruce Marshall]]\n| ''[[The Red Danube]]'' (1949)\n|-\n| ''[[The Vicomte of Bragelonne: Ten Years Later]]'' (''The Vicomte of Bragelonne: Ten Years Later'') (1847\u20131850), [[Alexandre Dumas, p\u00e8re]]\n| ''[[The Iron Mask]]'' (1929)<br />''[[The Man in the Iron Mask (1939 film)|The Man in the Iron Mask]]'' (1939)<br />''[[The Man in the Iron Mask (1977 film)|The Man in the Iron Mask]]'' (1977)<br />''[[The Man in the Iron Mask (1998 film)|The Man in the Iron Mask]]'' (1998)\n|-\n| ''[[Victory (novel)|Victory]]'' (1915), [[Joseph Conrad]]\n| ''[[Victory (1919 film)|Victory]]'' (1919)<br />''[[Victory (novel)#Film, TV or theatrical adaptations - Niebezpieczny raj (Dangerous Paradise, 1930)|Niebezpieczny raj]]'' (''Dangerous Paradise'') (1930)<br />''[[Victory (novel)#Film, TV or theatrical adaptations - Dangerous Paradise (1930 film)|Dangerous Paradise]]'' (1930)<br />''[[Frederic March#Filmography and awards|Victo