]]'' (1983), [[Susan Hill]]\n| ''[[The Woman in Black (1989 film)|The Woman in Black]]'' (1989) (TV)<br />''[[The Woman in Black (2012 film)|The Woman in Black]]'' (2012)\n|-\n| ''[[The Woman in White (novel)|The Woman in White]]'' (1859\u20131860) (serial), (1860) (novel), [[Wilkie Collins]]\n| ''[[The Woman in White (novel)#Adaptations - Film and television - 1912 American silent film|The Woman in White]]'' (1912/I)<br />''[[The Woman in White (novel)#Adaptations - Film and television - 1912 American silent film|The Woman in White]]'' (1912/II)<br />''[[The Woman in White (novel)#Adaptations - Film and television - 1917 American silent film|The Woman in White]]'' (1917)<br />''[[The Woman in White (novel)#Adaptations - Film and television - 1929 British silent film adapted by Robert Cullen starring Haddon Mason as Walter Hartright and Louise Prussing as Marian Halcombe|The Woman in White]]'' (1929)<br />''[[Crimes at the Dark House]]'' (1940)<br />''[[The Woman in White (1948 film)|The Woman in White]]'' (1948)<br />''[[The Woman in White (novel)#Adaptations - Film and television - 1982 BBC miniseries adapted by Ray Jenkins starring Daniel Gerroll as Walter Hartright and Diana Quick as Marian Halcombe|The Woman in Black]]'' (1982) (TV) (mini)<br />''[[The Woman in White (novel)#Adaptations - Film and television - 1982 Soviet film under the Russian title Zhenshchina v belom, directed by Vadim Derbenyov and starring Aleksandr Abdulov as Walter Hartright and Lithuanian actress Gra\u017eina Baik\u0161tyt\u0117 as both Laura Fairlie and Anne Catherick|Zhenshchina v belom]]'' (1982)\n|-\n| ''Woman, Thou Art Loosed!: Healings the Wounds of the Past'' (1993), [[T. D. Jakes]]\n| ''[[Woman Thou Art Loosed]]'' (2004)\n|-\n| ''Woman Wanted'' (1984), [[Joanna McClelland Glass]]\n| ''[[Woman Wanted]]'' (2000)\n|-\n| ''[[Women in Love]]'' (1920), [[D. H. Lawrence]]\n| ''[[Women in Love (film)|Women in Love]]'' (1969)\n|-\n| ''[[The Women of Brewster Place (novel)|The Women of Br